x25gwIdTable.name: x25gwIdTable
x25gwIdTable.description: A table that contains information that identifies the hardware and software that make up the specified X.25 card.

x25gwIdEntry.name: x25gwIdEntry
x25gwIdEntry.description: There is one entry in this table for every X.25 card in the chassis.

x25gwIdIndex.name: x25gwIdIndex
x25gwIdIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies the X.25 card for which this row in the table pertains. The value of this index matches the value of the index for the corresponding entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

x25gwIdHardwareSerNum.name: x25gwIdHardwareSerNum
x25gwIdHardwareSerNum.description: The X.25 card's hardware serial number as stored in EEPROM.

x25gwIdHardwareRev.name: x25gwIdHardwareRev
x25gwIdHardwareRev.description: The hardware revision of the specified X.25 card as stored in its EEPROM.

x25gwIdSoftwareRev.name: x25gwIdSoftwareRev
x25gwIdSoftwareRev.description: The revision of the software being executed in the specified X.25 card.

x25gwIdCpuType.name: x25gwIdCpuType
x25gwIdCpuType.description: Defines the type of CPU present on the X.25 Gateway NAC.

x25gwIdRamInstalled.name: x25gwIdRamInstalled
x25gwIdRamInstalled.description: Specifies the amount of DRAM installed on the X.25 Gateway NAC in Kbytes.

x25gwIdFlashInstalled.name: x25gwIdFlashInstalled
x25gwIdFlashInstalled.description: Specifies the amount of Flash Rom installed on the X.25 Gateway NAC in Kbytes.

x25gwIdOperCfgSts.name: x25gwIdOperCfgSts
x25gwIdOperCfgSts.description: Informs the operator as to whether the operational parameters are the NVRAM parameters or if the administrative parameters have been saved to NVRAM.

x25gwIdSelfTestResult.name: x25gwIdSelfTestResult
x25gwIdSelfTestResult.description: Displays the results of the most resent self test performed by the X.25 Gateway NAC. If all tests have passed a value of 0 is returned.

x25gwIdMgmtConnect.name: x25gwIdMgmtConnect
x25gwIdMgmtConnect.description: Indicates the current status of X.25 gateway user interface.

x25gwCmdTable.name: x25gwCmdTable
x25gwCmdTable.description: The X.25 Card Command table contains an entry for each of the manageable X.25 Cards in the chassis. It provides a means through which to take specific actions on one or more X.25 cards in the NAS chassis. The number of entries in this table is given by the value of x25gwIdNumber.

x25gwCmdEntry.name: x25gwCmdEntry
x25gwCmdEntry.description: There is one X.25 Card Command entry per X.25 Card in the chassis.

x25gwCmdIndex.name: x25gwCmdIndex
x25gwCmdIndex.description: A unique value for each X.25 Card in the chassis. The value of this object matches the value of the index of the corresponding X.25 Card's entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

x25gwCmdMgtStationId.name: x25gwCmdMgtStationId
x25gwCmdMgtStationId.description: This object is a generic read-write variable that a Management Station (MS) can use to guarantee that the results from a given command are the results of a command issued by that specific MS. Each MS must SET a unique value to this object when doing commands and GET the value of this object together with x25gwCmdReqId and x25gwCmdResult to detect interference from other MSs.

x25gwCmdReqId.name: x25gwCmdReqId
x25gwCmdReqId.description: This object contains the value of the request-id field in the SNMP PDU which invoked the current or most recent command or test on this X.25 Card. If the request-id is unknown or undefined, this object contains the value zero.

x25gwCmdFunction.name: x25gwCmdFunction
x25gwCmdFunction.description: This object contains a value which describes the command which is being invoked.

x25gwCmdForce.name: x25gwCmdForce
x25gwCmdForce.description: In some cases, the X.25 Card may be in a state such that certain commands could adversely affect connections. In such cases, a command request with this object not present or set to noForce will result in a warning. If the operator elects to ignore such warnings, this object can be set to force in a subsequent issue of the command to cause the command to be carried out regardless of its potentially hazzardous effects.

x25gwCmdParam.name: x25gwCmdParam
x25gwCmdParam.description: This object contains parameters that are specific to the particular command being issued. In some cases, there will be no aditional parameters required.

x25gwCmdResult.name: x25gwCmdResult
x25gwCmdResult.description: This object contains the result of the most recently requested command or test, or the value none(1) if no commands have been requested since the last reset.

x25gwCmdCode.name: x25gwCmdCode
x25gwCmdCode.description: The Value of this object is value of this object is noError(1) if the command was successful, and indicates a further description of what went wrong if it was unsuccessful.

x25gwCfgTable.name: x25gwCfgTable
x25gwCfgTable.description: A table of configurable parameters specific to the X.25 Gateway NAC.

x25gwCfgIndex.name: x25gwCfgIndex
x25gwCfgIndex.description: A unique value for each X.25 NAC installed in the chassis. The value of this index is identical to the index in the USR chassis MIB associates with the X.25 Gateway Card entity.

x25gwCfgUiPort.name: x25gwCfgUiPort
x25gwCfgUiPort.description: Defines how the user interface port on the X.25 NIC will be used. When configured for PAD access the UI port will provide a means of accessing the X.25 network via a direct connected serial device.

x25gwCfgLocModemConn.name: x25gwCfgLocModemConn
x25gwCfgLocModemConn.description: Defines whether the gateway UI access will be via direct attachment or by Dial up Modem.

x25gwCfgRoutingType.name: x25gwCfgRoutingType
x25gwCfgRoutingType.description: Determines the means by which X.25 call will be routed to the NMC or modem. Default=None(1).

x25gwCfgCudRoutStr.name: x25gwCfgCudRoutStr
x25gwCfgCudRoutStr.description: Call user data string is used to compare to the incoming X.25 call request CUD. If they match then the call is routed to the NMC. Default=MGMTOVX25.

x25gwCfgX121SubAddr.name: x25gwCfgX121SubAddr
x25gwCfgX121SubAddr.description: X.121 Subaddress is used to compare to the incoming X.25 call request Subaddress. If they match then the call is routed to the NMC. Default=99.

x25gwTrapEnaTable.name: x25gwTrapEnaTable
x25gwTrapEnaTable.description: Table containing objects to enable traps on the X.25 Cards in the chassis.

x25gwTrapEnaEntry.name: x25gwTrapEnaEntry
x25gwTrapEnaEntry.description: There is one entry for each X.25 Card in the chassis.

x25gwTrapEnaIndex.name: x25gwTrapEnaIndex
x25gwTrapEnaIndex.description: A unique index identifying the X.25 Card to which the trap enable objects pertain.

x25gwTrapEnaUiReset.name: x25gwTrapEnaUiReset
x25gwTrapEnaUiReset.description: Enables reporting of NAC Reset by user interface command traps. Default=disable(2).
